Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. records.addlTxt: Response from Court to Behavioral Consultants Inc in regards to defendants competency exam w/ fax sheet confirmation

9:31 AM Defendant Ricardo R Tzinzun in court.  Attorney Emily M Nolan-Plutchak in court for Ricardo R Tzinzun.  Prosecuting attorney Craig Lambert in court for the State of Wisconsin. 
Court addresses the reason the defendant hasn't been appearing for his evaluation. Attorney Lambert is willing to give the defendant another chance at doing the evaluation outside of custody.
Court will allow and give the defendant one more chance to complete the evaluation otherwise will hold him in jail until it is completed and then will release him. This matter will be set for a status conference to get an update on the evaluation and it is mandatory that the defendant appears.
Status conference scheduled for November 8, 2022 at 02:30 pm.
Adjourned order to show cause hearing on October 12, 2022 at 09:30 am.

8:41 AM Defendant Ricardo R Tzinzun in court.  Attorney Emily M Nolan-Plutchak in court for Ricardo R Tzinzun.  Prosecuting attorney Craig Lambert in court for the State of Wisconsin. 
Attorney Nolan-Plutchak states this matter is going to be an NGI. This matter will be set for a different time. Bond is continued.

Defendant was in custody at the time of the hearing on 8/19/22. Attorney Knaapen asks that Court reinstate cash bond.

Court reinstates $1,000 cash bond.
Final pre-trial scheduled for August 19, 2022 at 09:00 am.

Court orders warrant. Cash bond may be forfeited.
Preliminary hearing and Arraignment on May 19, 2022 at 09:00 am.
